theorem closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → closure A = closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP1
  -- First, `closure (interior A)` is always contained in `closure A`
  have h₁ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
    have : interior A ⊆ A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  -- Second, `closure A` is contained in `closure (interior A)` thanks to `P1`
  have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have : A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      simpa [Topology.P1] using hP1
    exact closure_mono this
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₂ h₁
